<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer13713847207282745631">In the vein of <i>The Glass Castle</i>, <i>Breaking Night</i> is the stunning memoir of a young woman who at age fifteen was living on the streets, and who eventually made it into Harvard. <br/><br/>Liz Murray was born to loving but drug-addicted parents in the Bronx. In school she was taunted for her dirty clothing and lice-infested hair, eventually skipping so many classes that she was put into</span>
  <span id="freeText13713847207282745631" style="display:none">In the vein of <i>The Glass Castle</i>, <i>Breaking Night</i> is the stunning memoir of a young woman who at age fifteen was living on the streets, and who eventually made it into Harvard. <br /><br />Liz Murray was born to loving but drug-addicted parents in the Bronx. In school she was taunted for her dirty clothing and lice-infested hair, eventually skipping so many classes that she was put into a girls' home. At age fifteen, when her family finally unraveled, Murray found herself on the streets. She learned to scrape by, foraging for food and riding subways all night to have a warm place to sleep. <br /><br />Eventually, Murray decided to take control of her own destiny and go back to high school, often completing her assignments in the hallways and subway stations where she slept. She squeezed four years of high school into two, while homeless; won a <i>New York Times</i> scholarship; and made it into the Ivy League. <i>Breaking Night</i> is an unforgettable and beautifully written story of one young woman's indomitable spirit to survive and prevail, against all odds.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13713847207282745631" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

      </div>
</div>

