<div id="review_672545125" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/672545125" />
    <a title="Mariah Roze" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22371819-mariah-roze"><img alt="Mariah Roze" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1496763524p2/22371819.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/672545125?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mariah Roze" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mariah Roze" href="/user/show/22371819-mariah-roze">Mariah Roze</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer672545125" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11379273169180660556">I am so glad that this is the first book that I read for 2020. It was fantastic! Liz was so real about her life; her failures and accomplishments. I highly recommend this book!<br/><br/>&quot;Liz Murray was born to loving but drug-addicted parents in the Bronx. In school she was taunted for her dirty clothing and lice-infested hair, eventually skipping so many classes that she was put into a girls&apos; home. At age fifteen, when her family finally unraveled, Murray found herself on the streets. She learned to scra</span>
  <span id="freeText11379273169180660556" style="display:none">I am so glad that this is the first book that I read for 2020. It was fantastic! Liz was so real about her life; her failures and accomplishments. I highly recommend this book!<br /><br />"Liz Murray was born to loving but drug-addicted parents in the Bronx. In school she was taunted for her dirty clothing and lice-infested hair, eventually skipping so many classes that she was put into a girls' home. At age fifteen, when her family finally unraveled, Murray found herself on the streets. She learned to scrape by, foraging for food and riding subways all night to have a warm place to sleep.<br />Eventually, Murray decided to take control of her own destiny and go back to high school, often completing her assignments in the hallways and subway stations where she slept. She squeezed four years of high school into two, while homeless; won a New York Times scholarship; and made it into the Ivy League. Breaking Night is an unforgettable and beautifully written story of one young woman's indomitable spirit to survive and prevail, against all odds."</span>
  <a data-text-id="11379273169180660556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

