    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1123646606" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1123646606" />
    <a title="Dawn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5742040-dawn"><img alt="Dawn" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1123646606?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dawn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dawn" href="/user/show/5742040-dawn">Dawn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5742040-dawn?shelf=2015-books">2015-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5742040-dawn?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5742040-dawn?shelf=book-club-2015">book-club-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1123646606" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15390477664571866042">I wanted to be inspired by this book, but I felt like it was too heavy laden with experiences of her early life. I don&apos;t think she needed to include so many episodes of her youngest years to prove that her parents were so irresponsible with their lives. It was more depressing than inspirational for me and I couldn&apos;t get past the evidence of our failing welfare system. When government money could go to better education systems and programs to build better futures for children, a lack of checks an</span>
  <span id="freeText15390477664571866042" style="display:none">I wanted to be inspired by this book, but I felt like it was too heavy laden with experiences of her early life. I don't think she needed to include so many episodes of her youngest years to prove that her parents were so irresponsible with their lives. It was more depressing than inspirational for me and I couldn't get past the evidence of our failing welfare system. When government money could go to better education systems and programs to build better futures for children, a lack of checks and balances in the system allows the money to be squandered on drug addictions. That truth irritates me. <br /><br />The book wasn't without merit however. The illustration of different kinds of love was interesting. How she described that she knew her parents loved her because they went without food longer than they let her. But they didn't love her more than their next fix. <br /><br />The theme of second chances is intriguing as well. Liz's mother was given a second chance when she and Liz's father were caught in their prescription drug scheme. She didn't go to prison, and tried to be responsible with her children, until the father was released. Then it's obvious that the only relationship they had was with drugs. Then she squanders her second chance by going back down the same destructive path as before. Whereas Liz changes her life by working hard after her second chance comes in the form of an alternative high school. <br /><br />My biggest complaint about the book is that it takes so long to get to the uplifting stuff. It's several hundred pages of one bad decision after another, and I would have liked that to be summarized more, and the adult relationship with her sister to be fleshed out a little more. That's my prerogative though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15390477664571866042" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

